               Terms of Participation 
            h3 Participation Policy 
            | Participants in the  GIVIT Programme are required to comply with this policy.
            ol(style='list-style: decimal;')
              li
                strong Terminology
                br
                | Expressions defined in the GIVIT Programme - Terms & Conditions  have the same meaning in this policy.
              li
                strong Participants’ Obligations
                ol(style='list-style: none;')
                  li
                    | 2.1 Participants are  reminded that each Participant is participating in the GIVIT Programme on a  charitable basis. Accordingly, when participating in the GIVIT Programme,  Participants must be courteous and polite in their dealings with one another.  This includes being courteous and polite in all communication as well as being  punctual when collecting or delivering Items.
                    br
                  li
                    | 2.2 It is Participants  responsibility to ensure that the collection or delivery of Items is carried  out legally and safely.
              li
                strong Specific obligations  for GIVIT Charities
                ol(style='list-style: none;')
                  li
                    | 3.1 When requesting  that an Item be listed on the GIVIT List, GIVIT Charities must ensure that:
                    ul
                      li
                        | they have a client who  genuinely needs that Item now and to their knowledge does not intend  to sell  that Item, or it is an Item that will enable the GIVIT Charity to enhance the  service they provide to their clients;
                      li
                        | they are asking for an  Item that is needed (i.e. the Item will have a significant positive impact on  the recipient's quality of life, ability to become self-sufficient or enhance  their self-esteem);
                      li
                        | the Item is not  already listed on the Virtual Warehouse, unless the listed Item is not in close  proximity or the delivery method is not reasonably achievable for the GIVIT  Charity (e.g. the GIVIT Charity requires delivery when the listed Item requires  pick up);
                      li
                        | they have the means to  safely collect the Item if they indicate they can do so; and
                      li
                        | they have the means to  safely store the Item until it is collected or delivered to their client.
                  li
                    | 3.2 GIVIT Charities  must test and tag any electrical equipment donated via the GIVIT Portal before  providing it to their client.
                  li
                    | 3.3 GIVIT Charities  must assess the suitability of any Item for an intended client, including  whether the Item is safe.
                  li
                    | 3.4 GIVIT Charities must  not request that donated Items be delivered directly to their client. The  purpose of this is to protect the anonymity and safety of both the recipient  (i.e the GIVIT Charity's client) and the Donor, and to preserve the dignity of  the recipient.
                  li
                    | 3.5 GIVIT Charities  who request a service on behalf of a client must:
                    br
                    ul
                      li
                        | ensure a safe environment and/or workspace  for the service provider and client;
                      li
                        | be satisfied that the  service provider is suitably qualified, and in all other respects, fit to  provide the service; and
                      li
                        | if required and  necessary in the circumstances, obtain the recipient's consent to disclose any  personal information of the recipient in order for the service to be provided  to them.
                  li
                    | 3.6 GIVIT Charities  must not select an Item from the GIVIT Warehouse unless they can meet the  collection, delivery and/or storage requirements, if any, that are stipulated  or that are a direct consequence of selecting that Item.
