            p
              strong 7. Emergency response relief mode (hereinafter  referred to as “Emergency Mode”)
              br
              | In the event of an  emergency (e.g. bushfires, floods or other natural disasters) we may initiate  Emergency Mode for such period as determined by GIVIT.  During Emergency Mode there will be a dedicated  section in the GIVIT Portal to respond to such emergency, with an emergency  specific GIVIT List, and the following further terms and conditions apply  regarding Emergency Mode.
            ol(start='1', type='a')
              li
                strong (New Items only
                | )  Donors must only donate new Items requested  on the emergency GIVIT List.  This is a  necessary requirement, as in an emergency GIVIT Charities may not have time to check  that Items are safe and of appropriate quality.
              li
                | (
                strong Delivery Only within 48 hours): 
                | Donors       must only donate Items that can be delivered to the relevant delivery       point within 48 hours of making the donation, or that meets the delivery       window specified within the request for an Item.
              li
                | (
                strong Unappropriated donations
                | ) If there are any       unappropriated donations at the conclusion of an Emergency Mode, GIVIT may       apply these donations (whether it be Items and/ or cash) to the GIVIT       Programme.
            p
              strong
                br
              strong 8. Cash donations
            ol(style='list-style: lower-alpha;')
              li
                | (
                strong Cash donations
                | ) Donors may, in addition to donating Items, donate cash to  GIVIT to purchase Item/s on the GIVIT List or on a particular emergency GIVIT List.   Whilst Donors may choose to donate cash  towards Item/s on the GIVIT List or toward Item/s on a particular emergency  GIVIT List, Donors may not specify a particular Item/s that such donation shall  be used to procure.  All cash donated for  the purposes of meeting an emergency GIVIT List will be used for the purposes  purchasing Items requested as a result of the relevant emergency.  Should the cash donated exceed the amount  necessary to procure the requested items, clause 7 (c) shall apply.  Donors may also make cash donations for the  purpose of assisting GIVIT to meet its running costs.
